The Giants of Bordeaux 1970

HERE ARE THE ‘NOBLEST VINEYARDS OF THEM ALL.’ Vineyards that set the standard—not only for the red wines of Bordeaux, but for the red wines of the world. Here are clarets endowed with such power, balance and longevity that they will be alive and vibrant even two decades hence.

Just as an art collector attempts to buy Miro and Chagall shortly after the painting is completed in the fond expectation that he will not only enjoy its ownership, but relax in the certainty that the price will surely go up later—so, the knowledgeable wine collector acquires his ‘first growths’ shortly after a great vin- tage, knowing that he will either enjoy drinking the wines, or that they would cost considerably more had he chosen to ac- quire them later. 1970 IN BORDEAUX IS SUCH A VINTAGE.

TERMS AND INFORMATION — 1970 BORDEAUX

All of the 1970 red Bordeaux wines listed here will be available for delivery during 1973.

The prices quoted here include delivery charges to your home or warehouse of your choice, provided that it is within the vast United Parcel delivery zone (which includes New York City, Long Island, Westchester and parts of Rock- land and Orange counties).

If the delivery is beyond the United Parcel zone, but within New York State, there will be no charge for delivery if any single shipment is in excess of $150 (if below $150 there will be a charge of $9.50 for each shipment to an upstate address).

Kindly add the appropriate sales tax prevailing at the time of purchase and in your area.

Check in payment must accompany order.

If the wine that you order is in excess of the storage space in your home, your purchase can be stored by you, in warehouse cellars that can be recom- mended highly. On inquiry, we will gladly advise you of prevailing storage rates.

The 1970 vintage is available in half-bottles and magnums at $3.00 per case additional.
